Interference of various amino acids and biomolecules in the quenching nature of Tyr towards the fluorescence of probe (Fig. 5
                        ) was studied (concentration of I2 = 14 μM and 2.614 μM of aminoacids and biomolecules). The experimental results proves that Tyr has better sensitivity towards turn-off nature in the presence of possible interferents. Out of the 20 amino acids, only Tyr contain pheonlic OH group. The NCDs undergo strong electrostatic interaction with I3
                        − ion [33]. This system together interact with Tyr and undergo further quenching of fluorescence of NCDs.
